sql:
SELECT temperature, wind
FROM weather_forecasts
WHERE station_id = 0 AND forecast_time > strftime('%s', 'now') + 3600;

SELECT * 
FROM weather_forecasts 
WHERE CAST(SUBSTR(wind, 1, INSTR(wind, ' ') - 1) AS REAL) > (SELECT AVG(speed_value) FROM wind_speeds);

external_knowledge:
- Significant height: greater than 1500 meters;
- Dealing with clouds: implies working with cloud height data;
- Active meteorologists: those with active user accounts;
- Haven't accessed any stations: no records in the access logs.

- Navigators: users who are actively accessing data; 
- Lighthouses: weather stations; 
- Signals: represent the type of data access (view, download); 
- Guiding the seas: refers to active user accounts (is_active = 1); 
- Time of signals: access time when the data was accessed.

sql:
SELECT ws.station_name, ww.warning_message
FROM weather_stations ws
JOIN weather_warnings ww ON ws.station_id = ww.station_id;

SELECT AVG(precipitation) AS average_precipitation
FROM weather_data
WHERE time = 'SPECIFY_TIME_HERE';

SELECT users.user_name, weather_stations.station_name
FROM users, weather_stations
WHERE users.user_id = weather_stations.station_id;
